    <body>
        <p>This feature is based on a bookmark named "CoverImage." All source and Manual target templates provided by <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> have this bookmark, and it is placed by default on the cover image at the beginning of the template. However, if you specify a different image in the Help Targets dialog, it will replace the default cover image that is embedded in the target template.</p>
        <p>To define a new location for the cover image, you can edit the template<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Templates/D2H/Editing a Template.htm">Editing a Template</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>, inserting a bookmark named "CoverImage" somewhere before the "ChapterHeading" bookmark (if it exists). Otherwise, the image will be inserted at the beginning of the document.</p>
    </body>
</html>